   BSDR_PLUGIN_ABI constant, and the bsdr_plugin_register() entry point —
   and nothing else. The Plugin API deliberately requires a plugin to link
   against no symbol of the host binary: every host service is reached
   through function pointers supplied to the plugin at run time.

   "Plugin" means a separate and independent work, in the form of a
   dynamically loadable module (a shared object or dynamic library), that is
   designed to be loaded by the Program at run time and that interacts with
